oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Letter from Sgt. Carl Cecil Braden to Mrs. W.W. Braden, 1919 February 7
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This letter, with envelope, from Sgt. Carl Cecil Braden, HQ Troop, 82nd Div. to Mrs. W.W. Braden in Lewisburg, Tenn. is written on unlined American Red Cross letterhead paper. It is dated Feb 7, 1919. Braden describes some of his preparations for returning home including having photographs made in Dijon, France. Sgt. Carl C. Braden, Hq. Troop 82nd Div.
